  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 51ee3e37f5ded7941ab6216610f6fc67, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: Prologue
      content: '  This is a revelation from[[COMMENT(0)]] Jesus Christ, which God
        gave him to show his servants the events that must soon[[COMMENT(1)]] take
        place. He sent an angel to present this revelation to his servant John, '
      comments:
      - number: '1:1a '
        content: Or <b>of.</b>
      - number: '1:1b '
        content: Or <b>suddenly, </b>or <b>quickly.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'who faithfully reported everything he saw. This is his report of
        the word of God and the testimony of Jesus Christ.  '
      comments: []
    - title: "John\u2019s Greeting to the Seven Churches"
      content: 'God blesses the one who reads the words of this prophecy to the church,
        and he blesses all who listen to its message and obey what it says, for the
        time is near.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This letter is from John to the seven churches in the province of
        Asia.[[COMMENT(0)]]Grace and peace to you from the one who is, who always
        was, and who is still to come; from the sevenfold Spirit[[COMMENT(1)]] before
        his throne; '
      comments:
      - number: '1:4a '
        content: <b>Asia </b>was a Roman province in what is now western Turkey.
      - number: '1:4b '
        content: Greek <b>the seven spirits.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'and from Jesus Christ. He is the faithful witness to these things,
        the first to rise from the dead, and the ruler of all the kings of the world.All
        glory to him who loves us and has freed us from our sins by shedding his
        blood for us. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He has made us a Kingdom of priests for God his Father. All glory
        and power to him forever and ever! Amen.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Look! He comes with the clouds of heaven.And everyone will see him\u2014even
        those who pierced him.And all the nations of the worldwill mourn for him.Yes!
        Amen!  "
      comments: []
    - title: Vision of the Son of Man
      content: "\u201CI am the Alpha and the Omega\u2014the beginning and the end,\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]
        says the Lord God. \u201CI am the one who is, who always was, and who is
        still to come\u2014the Almighty One.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:8 '
        content: Greek <b>I am the Alpha and the Omega, </b>referring to the first
          and last letters of the Greek alphabet.
    - title: 
      content: "I, John, am your brother and your partner in suffering and in God\u2019s
        Kingdom and in the patient endurance to which Jesus calls us. I was exiled
        to the island of Patmos for preaching the word of God and for my testimony
        about Jesus. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It was the Lord\u2019s Day, and I was worshiping in the Spirit.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Suddenly, I heard behind me a loud voice like a trumpet blast. "
      comments:
      - number: '1:10 '
        content: Or <b>in spirit.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "It said, \u201CWrite in a book[[COMMENT(0)]]  everything you see,
        and send it to the seven churches in the cities of Ephesus, Smyrna, Pergamum,
        Thyatira, Sardis, Philadelphia, and Laodicea.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:11 '
        content: Or <b>on a scroll.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'When I turned to see who was speaking to me, I saw seven gold lampstands. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And standing in the middle of the lampstands was someone like the
        Son of Man.[[COMMENT(0)]] He was wearing a long robe with a gold sash across
        his chest. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:13 '
        content: "Or <b>like a son of man. </b>See Dan 7:13. \u201CSon of Man\u201D
          is a title Jesus used for himself."
    - title: 
      content: 'His head and his hair were white like wool, as white as snow. And
        his eyes were like flames of fire. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'His feet were like polished bronze refined in a furnace, and his
        voice thundered like mighty ocean waves. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He held seven stars in his right hand, and a sharp two-edged sword
        came from his mouth. And his face was like the sun in all its brilliance.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When I saw him, I fell at his feet as if I were dead. But he laid
        his right hand on me and said, \u201CDon\u2019t be afraid! I am the First
        and the Last.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I am the living one. I died, but look\u2014I am alive forever and
        ever! And I hold the keys of death and the grave.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:18 '
        content: 'Greek <b>and Hades.</b>  '
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CWrite down what you have seen\u2014both the things that are
        now happening and the things that will happen.  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:19 '
        content: "  Or   <b>what you have seen and what they mean\u2014the things
          that have already begun to happen.</b>  "
  - verses:
    - title: The Message to the Church in Ephesus
      content: "    \u201CWrite this letter to the angel  [[COMMENT(0)]]  of the
        church in Ephesus. This is the message from the one who holds the seven stars
        in his right hand, the one who walks among the seven gold lampstands:  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:1 '
        content: '  Or   <b>the messenger; </b>  also in 2:8, 12, 18.    '
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CI know all the things you do. I have seen your hard work
        and your patient endurance. I know you don\u2019t tolerate evil people. You
        have examined the claims of those who say they are apostles but are not.
        You have discovered they are liars.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have patiently suffered for me without quitting.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CBut I have this complaint against you. You don\u2019t love
        me or each other as you did at first!  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:4 '
        content: '  Greek   <b>You have lost your first love.</b>    '
    - title: 
      content: "Look how far you have fallen! Turn back to me and do the works you
        did at first. If you don\u2019t repent, I will come and remove your lampstand
        from its place among the churches.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But this is in your favor: You hate the evil deeds of the Nicolaitans,
        just as I do.  '
      comments: []
    - title: The Message to the Church in Smyrna
      content: "  \u201CAnyone with ears to hear must listen to the Spirit and understand
        what he is saying to the churches. To everyone who is victorious I will give
        fruit from the tree of life in the paradise of God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CWrite this letter to the angel of the church in Smyrna. This
        is the message from the one who is the First and the Last, who was dead but
        is now alive:  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CI know about your suffering and your poverty\u2014but you
        are rich! I know the blasphemy of those opposing you. They say they are Jews,
        but they are not, because their synagogue belongs to Satan.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t be afraid of what you are about to suffer. The devil will
        throw some of you into prison to test you. You will suffer for ten days.
        But if you remain faithful even when facing death, I will give you the crown
        of life.  "
      comments: []
    - title: The Message to the Church in Pergamum
      content: "  \u201CAnyone with ears to hear must listen to the Spirit and understand
        what he is saying to the churches. Whoever is victorious will not be harmed
        by the second death.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CWrite this letter to the angel of the church in Pergamum.
        This is the message from the one with the sharp two-edged sword:  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CI know that you live in the city where Satan has his throne,
        yet you have remained loyal to me. You refused to deny me even when Antipas,
        my faithful witness, was martyred among you there in Satan\u2019s city.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CBut I have a few complaints against you. You tolerate some
        among you whose teaching is like that of Balaam, who showed Balak how to
        trip up the people of Israel. He taught them to sin by eating food offered
        to idols and by committing sexual sin.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In a similar way, you have some Nicolaitans among you who follow
        the same teaching.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Repent of your sin, or I will come to you suddenly and fight against
        them with the sword of my mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: The Message to the Church in Thyatira
      content: "  \u201CAnyone with ears to hear must listen to the Spirit and understand
        what he is saying to the churches. To everyone who is victorious I will give
        some of the manna that has been hidden away in heaven. And I will give to
        each one a white stone, and on the stone will be engraved a new name that
        no one understands except the one who receives it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CWrite this letter to the angel of the church in Thyatira.
        This is the message from the Son of God, whose eyes are like flames of fire,
        whose feet are like polished bronze:  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CI know all the things you do. I have seen your love, your
        faith, your service, and your patient endurance. And I can see your constant
        improvement in all these things.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CBut I have this complaint against you. You are permitting
        that woman\u2014that Jezebel who calls herself a prophet\u2014to lead my
        servants astray. She teaches them to commit sexual sin and to eat food offered
        to idols.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I gave her time to repent, but she does not want to turn away from
        her immorality.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CTherefore, I will throw her on a bed of suffering,  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        and those who commit adultery with her will suffer greatly unless they repent
        and turn away from her evil deeds.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:22 '
        content: '  Greek   <b>a bed.</b>    '
    - title: 
      content: 'I will strike her children dead. Then all the churches will know
        that I am the one who searches out the thoughts and intentions of every person.
        And I will give to each of you whatever you deserve.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CBut I also have a message for the rest of you in Thyatira
        who have not followed this false teaching (\u2018deeper truths,\u2019 as
        they call them\u2014depths of Satan, actually). I will ask nothing more of
        you  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'except that you hold tightly to what you have until I come.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'To all who are victorious, who obey me to the very end,  To them
        I will give authority over all the nations.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: '  They will rule the nations with an iron rod  and smash them like
        clay pots.  [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:26-27 '
        content: '  Ps 2:8-9 (Greek version).  '
    - title: 
      content: '  They will have the same authority I received from my Father, and
        I will also give them the morning star!  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Message to the Church in Sardis
      content: "    \u201CWrite this letter to the angel  [[COMMENT(0)]]  of the
        church in Sardis. This is the message from the one who has the sevenfold
        Spirit[[COMMENT(1)]]  of God and the seven stars:  \u201CI know all the things
        you do, and that you have a reputation for being alive\u2014but you are dead.  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:1a '
        content: '  Or   <b>the messenger; </b>  also in 3:7, 14.  '
      - number: '3:1b '
        content: 'Greek <b>the seven spirits.</b>  '
    - title: 
      content: 'Wake up! Strengthen what little remains, for even what is left is
        almost dead. I find that your actions do not meet the requirements of my
        God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Go back to what you heard and believed at first; hold to it firmly.
        Repent and turn to me again. If you don\u2019t wake up, I will come to you
        suddenly, as unexpected as a thief.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CYet there are some in the church in Sardis who have not soiled
        their clothes with evil. They will walk with me in white, for they are worthy.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'All who are victorious will be clothed in white. I will never erase
        their names from the Book of Life, but I will announce before my Father and
        his angels that they are mine.  '
      comments: []
    - title: The Message to the Church in Philadelphia
      content: "  \u201CAnyone with ears to hear must listen to the Spirit and understand
        what he is saying to the churches.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CWrite this letter to the angel of the church in Philadelphia. 
        This is the message from the one who is holy and true,  the one who has the
        key of David.  What he opens, no one can close;  and what he closes, no one
        can open:  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:7 '
        content: '  Isa 22:22.  '
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CI know all the things you do, and I have opened a door for
        you that no one can close. You have little strength, yet you obeyed my word
        and did not deny me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Look, I will force those who belong to Satan\u2019s synagogue\u2014those
        liars who say they are Jews but are not\u2014to come and bow down at your
        feet. They will acknowledge that you are the ones I love.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CBecause you have obeyed my command to persevere, I will protect
        you from the great time of testing that will come upon the whole world to
        test those who belong to this world.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am coming soon.[[COMMENT(0)]]  Hold on to what you have, so that
        no one will take away your crown.  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:11 '
        content: 'Or <b>suddenly</b>, or <b>quickly.</b>  '
    - title: 
      content: "All who are victorious will become pillars in the Temple of my God,
        and they will never have to leave it. And I will write on them the name of
        my God, and they will be citizens in the city of my God\u2014the new Jerusalem
        that comes down from heaven from my God. And I will also write on them my
        new name.  "
      comments: []
    - title: The Message to the Church in Laodicea
      content: "  \u201CAnyone with ears to hear must listen to the Spirit and understand
        what he is saying to the churches.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CWrite this letter to the angel of the church in Laodicea.
        This is the message from the one who is the Amen\u2014the faithful and true
        witness, the beginning  [[COMMENT(0)]]  of God\u2019s new creation:  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:14 '
        content: '  Or   <b>the ruler, </b>  or   <b>the source.</b>  '
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CI know all the things you do, that you are neither hot nor
        cold. I wish that you were one or the other!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But since you are like lukewarm water, neither hot nor cold, I will
        spit you out of my mouth!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You say, \u2018I am rich. I have everything I want. I don\u2019t
        need a thing!\u2019 And you don\u2019t realize that you are wretched and
        miserable and poor and blind and naked.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So I advise you to buy gold from me\u2014gold that has been purified
        by fire. Then you will be rich. Also buy white garments from me so you will
        not be shamed by your nakedness, and ointment for your eyes so you will be
        able to see.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I correct and discipline everyone I love. So be diligent and turn
        from your indifference.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CLook! I stand at the door and knock. If you hear my voice
        and open the door, I will come in, and we will share a meal together as friends.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Those who are victorious will sit with me on my throne, just as I
        was victorious and sat with my Father on his throne.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Worship in Heaven
      content: "  Then as I looked, I saw a door standing open in heaven, and the
        same voice I had heard before spoke to me like a trumpet blast. The voice
        said, \u201CCome up here, and I will show you what must happen after this.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And instantly I was in the Spirit,[[COMMENT(0)]] and I saw a throne
        in heaven and someone sitting on it. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:2 '
        content: Or <b>in spirit.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "The one sitting on the throne was as brilliant as gemstones\u2014like
        jasper and carnelian. And the glow of an emerald circled his throne like
        a rainbow. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Twenty-four thrones surrounded him, and twenty-four elders sat on
        them. They were all clothed in white and had gold crowns on their heads. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'From the throne came flashes of lightning and the rumble of thunder.
        And in front of the throne were seven torches with burning flames. This is
        the sevenfold Spirit[[COMMENT(0)]] of God. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:5 '
        content: Greek <b>They are the seven spirits.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'In front of the throne was a shiny sea of glass, sparkling like crystal.In
        the center and around the throne were four living beings, each covered with
        eyes, front and back. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The first of these living beings was like a lion; the second was
        like an ox; the third had a human face; and the fourth was like an eagle
        in flight. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Each of these living beings had six wings, and their wings were covered
        all over with eyes, inside and out. Day after day and night after night they
        keep on saying,\u201CHoly, holy, holy is the Lord God, the Almighty\u2014the
        one who always was, who is, and who is still to come.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Whenever the living beings give glory and honor and thanks to the
        one sitting on the throne (the one who lives forever and ever), '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'the twenty-four elders fall down and worship the one sitting on the
        throne (the one who lives forever and ever). And they lay their crowns before
        the throne and say,  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Lamb Opens the Scroll
      content: '  Then I saw a scroll[[COMMENT(0)]] in the right hand of the one
        who was sitting on the throne. There was writing on the inside and the outside
        of the scroll, and it was sealed with seven seals. '
      comments:
      - number: '5:1 '
        content: Or <b>book; </b>also in 5:2, 3, 4, 5, 7, 8, 9.
    - title: 
      content: "And I saw a strong angel, who shouted with a loud voice: \u201CWho
        is worthy to break the seals on this scroll and open it?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But no one in heaven or on earth or under the earth was able to open
        the scroll and read it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then I began to weep bitterly because no one was found worthy to
        open the scroll and read it. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But one of the twenty-four elders said to me, \u201CStop weeping!
        Look, the Lion of the tribe of Judah, the heir to David\u2019s throne,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        has won the victory. He is worthy to open the scroll and its seven seals.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:5 '
        content: Greek <b>the root of David. </b>See Isa 11:10.
    - title: 
      content: 'Then I saw a Lamb that looked as if it had been slaughtered, but
        it was now standing between the throne and the four living beings and among
        the twenty-four elders. He had seven horns and seven eyes, which represent
        the sevenfold Spirit[[COMMENT(0)]] of God that is sent out into every part
        of the earth. '
      comments:
      - number: '5:6 '
        content: Greek <b>which are the seven spirits.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'He stepped forward and took the scroll from the right hand of the
        one sitting on the throne. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And when he took the scroll, the four living beings and the twenty-four
        elders fell down before the Lamb. Each one had a harp, and they held gold
        bowls filled with incense, which are the prayers of God\u2019s people. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And they sang a new song with these words:\u201CYou are worthy to
        take the scrolland break its seals and open it.For you were slaughtered,
        and your blood has ransomed people for Godfrom every tribe and language and
        people and nation.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And you have caused them to becomea Kingdom of priests for our God.And
        they will reign[[COMMENT(0)]] on the earth.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:10 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>they are reigning.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Then I looked again, and I heard the voices of thousands and millions
        of angels around the throne and of the living beings and the elders. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And they sang in a mighty chorus:\u201CWorthy is the Lamb who was
        slaughtered\u2014to receive power and richesand wisdom and strengthand honor
        and glory and blessing.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And then I heard every creature in heaven and on earth and under
        the earth and in the sea. They sang:\u201CBlessing and honor and glory and
        powerbelong to the one sitting on the throneand to the Lamb forever and ever.\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Lamb Breaks the First Six Seals
      content: "  As I watched, the Lamb broke the first of the seven seals on the
        scroll.[[COMMENT(0)]] Then I heard one of the four living beings say with
        a voice like thunder, \u201CCome!\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '6:1 '
        content: Or <b>book.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'I looked up and saw a white horse standing there. Its rider carried
        a bow, and a crown was placed on his head. He rode out to win many battles
        and gain the victory.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When the Lamb broke the second seal, I heard the second living being
        say, \u201CCome!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then another horse appeared, a red one. Its rider was given a mighty
        sword and the authority to take peace from the earth. And there was war and
        slaughter everywhere.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When the Lamb broke the third seal, I heard the third living being
        say, \u201CCome!\u201D I looked up and saw a black horse, and its rider was
        holding a pair of scales in his hand. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And I heard a voice from among the four living beings say, \u201CA
        loaf of wheat bread or three loaves of barley will cost a day\u2019s pay.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        And don\u2019t waste[[COMMENT(1)]] the olive oil and wine.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:6a '
        content: "Greek <b>A choinix </b>[1 quart or 1 liter] <b>of wheat for a denarius,
          and 3 choinix of barley for a denarius. </b>A denarius was equivalent to
          a laborer\u2019s full day\u2019s wage."
      - number: '6:6b '
        content: Or <b>harm.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "When the Lamb broke the fourth seal, I heard the fourth living being
        say, \u201CCome!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I looked up and saw a horse whose color was pale green. Its rider
        was named Death, and his companion was the Grave.[[COMMENT(0)]] These two
        were given authority over one-fourth of the earth, to kill with the sword
        and famine and disease[[COMMENT(1)]] and wild animals.  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:8a '
        content: Greek <b>was Hades.</b>
      - number: '6:8b '
        content: Greek <b>death.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'When the Lamb broke the fifth seal, I saw under the altar the souls
        of all who had been martyred for the word of God and for being faithful in
        their testimony. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They shouted to the Lord and said, \u201CO Sovereign Lord, holy and
        true, how long before you judge the people who belong to this world and avenge
        our blood for what they have done to us?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then a white robe was given to each of them. And they were told to
        rest a little longer until the full number of their brothers and sisters[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014their
        fellow servants of Jesus who were to be martyred\u2014had joined them.  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:11 '
        content: Greek <b>their brothers.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'I watched as the Lamb broke the sixth seal, and there was a great
        earthquake. The sun became as dark as black cloth, and the moon became as
        red as blood. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the stars of the sky fell to the earth like green figs falling
        from a tree shaken by a strong wind. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The sky was rolled up like a scroll, and all of the mountains and
        islands were moved from their places.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then everyone\u2014the kings of the earth, the rulers, the generals,
        the wealthy, the powerful, and every slave and free person\u2014all hid themselves
        in the caves and among the rocks of the mountains. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And they cried to the mountains and the rocks, \u201CFall on us and
        hide us from the face of the one who sits on the throne and from the wrath
        of the Lamb. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "God\u2019s People Will Be Preserved"
      content: '  Then I saw four angels standing at the four corners of the earth,
        holding back the four winds so they did not blow on the earth or the sea,
        or even on any tree. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And I saw another angel coming up from the east, carrying the seal
        of the living God. And he shouted to those four angels, who had been given
        power to harm land and sea, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWait! Don\u2019t harm the land or the sea or the trees until
        we have placed the seal of God on the foreheads of his servants.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And I heard how many were marked with the seal of God\u2014144,000
        were sealed from all the tribes of Israel:"
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: from Judah12,000from Reuben12,000from Gad12,000
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: from Asher12,000from Naphtali12,000from Manasseh12,000
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: from Simeon12,000from Levi12,000from Issachar12,000
      comments: []
    - title: Praise from the Great Crowd
      content: 'from Zebulun12,000from Joseph12,000from Benjamin12,000  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'After this I saw a vast crowd, too great to count, from every nation
        and tribe and people and language, standing in front of the throne and before
        the Lamb. They were clothed in white robes and held palm branches in their
        hands. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And they were shouting with a great roar,\u201CSalvation comes from
        our God who sits on the throneand from the Lamb!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And all the angels were standing around the throne and around the
        elders and the four living beings. And they fell before the throne with their
        faces to the ground and worshiped God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They sang,\u201CAmen! Blessing and glory and wisdomand thanksgiving
        and honorand power and strength belong to our Godforever and ever! Amen.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then one of the twenty-four elders asked me, \u201CWho are these
        who are clothed in white? Where did they come from?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And I said to him, \u201CSir, you are the one who knows.\u201DThen
        he said to me, \u201CThese are the ones who died in[[COMMENT(0)]] the great
        tribulation.[[COMMENT(1)]] They have washed their robes in the blood of the
        Lamb and made them white.  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:14a '
        content: Greek <b>who came out of.</b>
      - number: '7:14b '
        content: Or <b>the great suffering.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThat is why they stand in front of God\u2019s throneand serve
        him day and night in his Temple.And he who sits on the thronewill give them
        shelter.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will never again be hungry or thirsty;they will never be scorched
        by the heat of the sun.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Lamb Breaks the Seventh Seal
      content: '  When the Lamb broke the seventh seal on the scroll,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        there was silence throughout heaven for about half an hour. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:1 '
        content: Or <b>book.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'I saw the seven angels who stand before God, and they were given
        seven trumpets.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then another angel with a gold incense burner came and stood at the
        altar. And a great amount of incense was given to him to mix with the prayers
        of God\u2019s people as an offering on the gold altar before the throne. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The smoke of the incense, mixed with the prayers of God\u2019s holy
        people, ascended up to God from the altar where the angel had poured them
        out. "
      comments: []
    - title: The First Four Trumpets
      content: 'Then the angel filled the incense burner with fire from the altar
        and threw it down upon the earth; and thunder crashed, lightning flashed,
        and there was a terrible earthquake.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the seven angels with the seven trumpets prepared to blow their
        mighty blasts.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The first angel blew his trumpet, and hail and fire mixed with blood
        were thrown down on the earth. One-third of the earth was set on fire, one-third
        of the trees were burned, and all the green grass was burned.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the second angel blew his trumpet, and a great mountain of fire
        was thrown into the sea. One-third of the water in the sea became blood, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'one-third of all things living in the sea died, and one-third of
        all the ships on the sea were destroyed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the third angel blew his trumpet, and a great star fell from
        the sky, burning like a torch. It fell on one-third of the rivers and on
        the springs of water. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The name of the star was Bitterness.[[COMMENT(0)]] It made one-third
        of the water bitter, and many people died from drinking the bitter water.  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:11 '
        content: Greek <b>Wormwood.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the fourth angel blew his trumpet, and one-third of the sun
        was struck, and one-third of the moon, and one-third of the stars, and they
        became dark. And one-third of the day was dark, and also one-third of the
        night.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Fifth Trumpet Brings the First Terror
      content: '  Then the fifth angel blew his trumpet, and I saw a star that had
        fallen to earth from the sky, and he was given the key to the shaft of the
        bottomless pit.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:1 '
        content: Or <b>the abyss, </b>or <b>the underworld; </b>also in 9:11.
    - title: 
      content: 'When he opened it, smoke poured out as though from a huge furnace,
        and the sunlight and air turned dark from the smoke.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then locusts came from the smoke and descended on the earth, and
        they were given power to sting like scorpions. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They were told not to harm the grass or plants or trees, but only
        the people who did not have the seal of God on their foreheads. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They were told not to kill them but to torture them for five months
        with pain like the pain of a scorpion sting. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In those days people will seek death but will not find it. They will
        long to die, but death will flee from them!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The locusts looked like horses prepared for battle. They had what
        looked like gold crowns on their heads, and their faces looked like human
        faces. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They had hair like women\u2019s hair and teeth like the teeth of
        a lion. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They wore armor made of iron, and their wings roared like an army
        of chariots rushing into battle. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They had tails that stung like scorpions, and for five months they
        had the power to torment people. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their king is the angel from the bottomless pit; his name in Hebrew
        is Abaddon, and in Greek, Apollyon\u2014the Destroyer.  "
      comments: []
    - title: The Sixth Trumpet Brings the Second Terror
      content: 'The first terror is past, but look, two more terrors are coming!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the sixth angel blew his trumpet, and I heard a voice speaking
        from the four horns of the gold altar that stands in the presence of God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And the voice said to the sixth angel who held the trumpet, \u201CRelease
        the four angels who are bound at the great Euphrates River.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the four angels who had been prepared for this hour and day
        and month and year were turned loose to kill one-third of all the people
        on earth. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I heard the size of their army, which was 200 million mounted troops.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And in my vision, I saw the horses and the riders sitting on them.
        The riders wore armor that was fiery red and dark blue and yellow. The horses
        had heads like lions, and fire and smoke and burning sulfur billowed from
        their mouths. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "One-third of all the people on earth were killed by these three plagues\u2014by
        the fire and smoke and burning sulfur that came from the mouths of the horses. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their power was in their mouths and in their tails. For their tails
        had heads like snakes, with the power to injure people.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the people who did not die in these plagues still refused to
        repent of their evil deeds and turn to God. They continued to worship demons
        and idols made of gold, silver, bronze, stone, and wood\u2014idols that can
        neither see nor hear nor walk! "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Angel and the Small Scroll
      content: '  Then I saw another mighty angel coming down from heaven, surrounded
        by a cloud, with a rainbow over his head. His face shone like the sun, and
        his feet were like pillars of fire. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And in his hand was a small scroll[[COMMENT(0)]] that had been opened.
        He stood with his right foot on the sea and his left foot on the land. '
      comments:
      - number: '10:2 '
        content: Or <b>book; </b>also in 10:8, 9, 10.
    - title: 
      content: 'And he gave a great shout like the roar of a lion. And when he shouted,
        the seven thunders answered.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When the seven thunders spoke, I was about to write. But I heard
        a voice from heaven saying, \u201CKeep secret[[COMMENT(0)]] what the seven
        thunders said, and do not write it down.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:4 '
        content: Greek <b>Seal up.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the angel I saw standing on the sea and on the land raised his
        right hand toward heaven. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He swore an oath in the name of the one who lives forever and ever,
        who created the heavens and everything in them, the earth and everything
        in it, and the sea and everything in it. He said, \u201CThere will be no
        more delay. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When the seventh angel blows his trumpet, God\u2019s mysterious plan
        will be fulfilled. It will happen just as he announced it to his servants
        the prophets.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the voice from heaven spoke to me again: \u201CGo and take the
        open scroll from the hand of the angel who is standing on the sea and on
        the land.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So I went to the angel and told him to give me the small scroll.
        \u201CYes, take it and eat it,\u201D he said. \u201CIt will be sweet as honey
        in your mouth, but it will turn sour in your stomach!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So I took the small scroll from the hand of the angel, and I ate
        it! It was sweet in my mouth, but when I swallowed it, it turned sour in
        my stomach.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Two Witnesses
      content: "  Then I was given a measuring stick, and I was told, \u201CGo and
        measure the Temple of God and the altar, and count the number of worshipers. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But do not measure the outer courtyard, for it has been turned over
        to the nations. They will trample the holy city for 42 months. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And I will give power to my two witnesses, and they will be clothed
        in burlap and will prophesy during those 1,260 days.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'These two prophets are the two olive trees and the two lampstands
        that stand before the Lord of all the earth. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If anyone tries to harm them, fire flashes from their mouths and
        consumes their enemies. This is how anyone who tries to harm them must die. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They have power to shut the sky so that no rain will fall for as
        long as they prophesy. And they have the power to turn the rivers and oceans
        into blood, and to strike the earth with every kind of plague as often as
        they wish.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When they complete their testimony, the beast that comes up out of
        the bottomless pit[[COMMENT(0)]] will declare war against them, and he will
        conquer them and kill them. '
      comments:
      - number: '11:7 '
        content: Or <b>the abyss, </b>or <b>the underworld.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "And their bodies will lie in the main street of Jerusalem,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        the city that is figuratively called \u201CSodom\u201D and \u201CEgypt,\u201D
        the city where their Lord was crucified. "
      comments:
      - number: '11:8 '
        content: Greek <b>the great city.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'And for three and a half days, all peoples, tribes, languages, and
        nations will stare at their bodies. No one will be allowed to bury them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'All the people who belong to this world will gloat over them and
        give presents to each other to celebrate the death of the two prophets who
        had tormented them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But after three and a half days, God breathed life into them, and
        they stood up! Terror struck all who were staring at them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then a loud voice from heaven called to the two prophets, \u201CCome
        up here!\u201D And they rose to heaven in a cloud as their enemies watched.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'At the same time there was a terrible earthquake that destroyed a
        tenth of the city. Seven thousand people died in that earthquake, and everyone
        else was terrified and gave glory to the God of heaven.  '
      comments: []
    - title: The Seventh Trumpet Brings the Third Terror
      content: 'The second terror is past, but look, the third terror is coming quickly.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the seventh angel blew his trumpet, and there were loud voices
        shouting in heaven:\u201CThe world has now become the Kingdom of our Lord
        and of his Christ,[[COMMENT(0)]]and he will reign forever and ever.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:15 '
        content: Or <b>his Messiah.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'The twenty-four elders sitting on their thrones before God fell with
        their faces to the ground and worshiped him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And they said,\u201CWe give thanks to you, Lord God, the Almighty,the
        one who is and who always was,for now you have assumed your great powerand
        have begun to reign.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The nations were filled with wrath,but now the time of your wrath
        has come.It is time to judge the deadand reward your servants the prophets,as
        well as your holy people,and all who fear your name,from the least to the
        greatest.It is time to destroyall who have caused destruction on the earth.\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Woman and the Dragon
      content: '  Then I witnessed in heaven an event of great significance. I saw
        a woman clothed with the sun, with the moon beneath her feet, and a crown
        of twelve stars on her head. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'She was pregnant, and she cried out because of her labor pains and
        the agony of giving birth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then I witnessed in heaven another significant event. I saw a large
        red dragon with seven heads and ten horns, with seven crowns on his heads. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'His tail swept away one-third of the stars in the sky, and he threw
        them to the earth. He stood in front of the woman as she was about to give
        birth, ready to devour her baby as soon as it was born.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'She gave birth to a son who was to rule all nations with an iron
        rod. And her child was snatched away from the dragon and was caught up to
        God and to his throne. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And the woman fled into the wilderness, where God had prepared a
        place to care for her for 1,260 days.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then there was war in heaven. Michael and his angels fought against
        the dragon and his angels. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And the dragon lost the battle, and he and his angels were forced
        out of heaven. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This great dragon\u2014the ancient serpent called the devil, or Satan,
        the one deceiving the whole world\u2014was thrown down to the earth with
        all his angels.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then I heard a loud voice shouting across the heavens,\u201CIt has
        come at last\u2014salvation and powerand the Kingdom of our God,and the authority
        of his Christ.[[COMMENT(0)]]For the accuser of our brothers and sisters[[COMMENT(1)]]has
        been thrown down to earth\u2014the one who accuses thembefore our God day
        and night.  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:10a '
        content: Or <b>his Messiah.</b>
      - number: '12:10b '
        content: Greek <b>brothers.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'And they have defeated him by the blood of the Lamband by their testimony.And
        they did not love their lives so muchthat they were afraid to die.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, rejoice, O heavens!And you who live in the heavens, rejoice!But
        terror will come on the earth and the sea,for the devil has come down to
        you in great anger,knowing that he has little time.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When the dragon realized that he had been thrown down to the earth,
        he pursued the woman who had given birth to the male child. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But she was given two wings like those of a great eagle so she could
        fly to the place prepared for her in the wilderness. There she would be cared
        for and protected from the dragon[[COMMENT(0)]] for a time, times, and half
        a time.  '
      comments:
      - number: '12:14 '
        content: Greek <b>the serpent; </b>also in 12:15. See 12:9.
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the dragon tried to drown the woman with a flood of water that
        flowed from his mouth. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the earth helped her by opening its mouth and swallowing the
        river that gushed out from the mouth of the dragon. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And the dragon was angry at the woman and declared war against the
        rest of her children\u2014all who keep God\u2019s commandments and maintain
        their testimony for Jesus.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Beast out of the Sea
      content: '  Then I saw a beast rising up out of the sea. It had seven heads
        and ten horns, with ten crowns on its horns. And written on each head were
        names that blasphemed God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This beast looked like a leopard, but it had the feet of a bear and
        the mouth of a lion! And the dragon gave the beast his own power and throne
        and great authority.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I saw that one of the heads of the beast seemed wounded beyond recovery\u2014but
        the fatal wound was healed! The whole world marveled at this miracle and
        gave allegiance to the beast. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They worshiped the dragon for giving the beast such power, and they
        also worshiped the beast. \u201CWho is as great as the beast?\u201D they
        exclaimed. \u201CWho is able to fight against him?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the beast was allowed to speak great blasphemies against God.
        And he was given authority to do whatever he wanted for forty-two months. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And he spoke terrible words of blasphemy against God, slandering
        his name and his dwelling\u2014that is, those who dwell in heaven.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '13:6 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>and his dwelling and all who dwell in heaven.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "And the beast was allowed to wage war against God\u2019s holy people
        and to conquer them. And he was given authority to rule over every tribe
        and people and language and nation. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And all the people who belong to this world worshiped the beast.
        They are the ones whose names were not written in the Book of Life that belongs
        to the Lamb who was slaughtered before the world was made.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:8 '
        content: "Or <b>not written in the Book of Life before the world was made\u2014the
          Book that belongs to the Lamb who was slaughtered.</b>"
    - title: 
      content: 'Anyone with ears to hearshould listen and understand.  '
      comments: []
    - title: The Beast out of the Earth
      content: "Anyone who is destined for prisonwill be taken to prison.Anyone destined
        to die by the swordwill die by the sword.This means that God\u2019s holy
        people must endure persecution patiently and remain faithful.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then I saw another beast come up out of the earth. He had two horns
        like those of a lamb, but he spoke with the voice of a dragon. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He exercised all the authority of the first beast. And he required
        all the earth and its people to worship the first beast, whose fatal wound
        had been healed. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He did astounding miracles, even making fire flash down to earth
        from the sky while everyone was watching. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And with all the miracles he was allowed to perform on behalf of
        the first beast, he deceived all the people who belong to this world. He
        ordered the people to make a great statue of the first beast, who was fatally
        wounded and then came back to life. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He was then permitted to give life to this statue so that it could
        speak. Then the statue of the beast commanded that anyone refusing to worship
        it must die.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He required everyone\u2014small and great, rich and poor, free and
        slave\u2014to be given a mark on the right hand or on the forehead. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And no one could buy or sell anything without that mark, which was
        either the name of the beast or the number representing his name. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Lamb and the 144,000
      content: "  Then I saw the Lamb standing on Mount Zion, and with him were 144,000
        who had his name and his Father\u2019s name written on their foreheads. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And I heard a sound from heaven like the roar of mighty ocean waves
        or the rolling of loud thunder. It was like the sound of many harpists playing
        together.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This great choir sang a wonderful new song in front of the throne
        of God and before the four living beings and the twenty-four elders. No one
        could learn this song except the 144,000 who had been redeemed from the earth. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They have kept themselves as pure as virgins,[[COMMENT(0)]] following
        the Lamb wherever he goes. They have been purchased from among the people
        on the earth as a special offering[[COMMENT(1)]] to God and to the Lamb. '
      comments:
      - number: '14:4a '
        content: Greek <b>They are virgins who have not defiled themselves with women.</b>
      - number: '14:4b '
        content: Greek <b>as firstfruits.</b>
    - title: The Three Angels
      content: 'They have told no lies; they are without blame.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And I saw another angel flying through the sky, carrying the eternal
        Good News to proclaim to the people who belong to this world\u2014to every
        nation, tribe, language, and people. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CFear God,\u201D he shouted. \u201CGive glory to him. For the
        time has come when he will sit as judge. Worship him who made the heavens,
        the earth, the sea, and all the springs of water.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then another angel followed him through the sky, shouting, \u201CBabylon
        is fallen\u2014that great city is fallen\u2014because she made all the nations
        of the world drink the wine of her passionate immorality.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then a third angel followed them, shouting, \u201CAnyone who worships
        the beast and his statue or who accepts his mark on the forehead or on the
        hand "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "must drink the wine of God\u2019s anger. It has been poured full
        strength into God\u2019s cup of wrath. And they will be tormented with fire
        and burning sulfur in the presence of the holy angels and the Lamb. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The smoke of their torment will rise forever and ever, and they will
        have no relief day or night, for they have worshiped the beast and his statue
        and have accepted the mark of his name.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This means that God\u2019s holy people must endure persecution patiently,
        obeying his commands and maintaining their faith in Jesus.  "
      comments: []
    - title: The Harvest of the Earth
      content: "And I heard a voice from heaven saying, \u201CWrite this down: Blessed
        are those who die in the Lord from now on. Yes, says the Spirit, they are
        blessed indeed, for they will rest from their hard work; for their good deeds
        follow them!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then I saw a white cloud, and seated on the cloud was someone like
        the Son of Man.[[COMMENT(0)]] He had a gold crown on his head and a sharp
        sickle in his hand.  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:14 '
        content: "Or <b>like a son of man. </b>See Dan 7:13. \u201CSon of Man\u201D
          is a title Jesus used for himself."
    - title: 
      content: "Then another angel came from the Temple and shouted to the one sitting
        on the cloud, \u201CSwing the sickle, for the time of harvest has come; the
        crop on earth is ripe.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So the one sitting on the cloud swung his sickle over the earth,
        and the whole earth was harvested.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'After that, another angel came from the Temple in heaven, and he
        also had a sharp sickle. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then another angel, who had power to destroy with fire, came from
        the altar. He shouted to the angel with the sharp sickle, \u201CSwing your
        sickle now to gather the clusters of grapes from the vines of the earth,
        for they are ripe for judgment.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So the angel swung his sickle over the earth and loaded the grapes
        into the great winepress of God\u2019s wrath. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Song of Moses and of the Lamb
      content: "  Then I saw in heaven another marvelous event of great significance.
        Seven angels were holding the seven last plagues, which would bring God\u2019s
        wrath to completion. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I saw before me what seemed to be a glass sea mixed with fire. And
        on it stood all the people who had been victorious over the beast and his
        statue and the number representing his name. They were all holding harps
        that God had given them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And they were singing the song of Moses, the servant of God, and
        the song of the Lamb:\u201CGreat and marvelous are your works,O Lord God,
        the Almighty.Just and true are your ways,O King of the nations.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '15:3 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>King of the ages.</b>
    - title: The Seven Bowls of the Seven Plagues
      content: "Who will not fear you, Lord,and glorify your name?For you alone are
        holy.All nations will come and worship before you,for your righteous deeds
        have been revealed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then I looked and saw that the Temple in heaven, God\u2019s Tabernacle,
        was thrown wide open. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The seven angels who were holding the seven plagues came out of the
        Temple. They were clothed in spotless white linen[[COMMENT(0)]] with gold
        sashes across their chests. '
      comments:
      - number: '15:6 '
        content: Other manuscripts read <b>white stone; </b>still others read <b>white
          [garments] made of linen.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Then one of the four living beings handed each of the seven angels
        a gold bowl filled with the wrath of God, who lives forever and ever. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "  Then I heard a mighty voice from the Temple say to the seven angels,
        \u201CGo your ways and pour out on the earth the seven bowls containing God\u2019s
        wrath.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So the first angel left the Temple and poured out his bowl on the
        earth, and horrible, malignant sores broke out on everyone who had the mark
        of the beast and who worshiped his statue.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the second angel poured out his bowl on the sea, and it became
        like the blood of a corpse. And everything in the sea died.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the third angel poured out his bowl on the rivers and springs,
        and they became blood. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And I heard the angel who had authority over all water saying,\u201CYou
        are just, O Holy One, who is and who always was,because you have sent these
        judgments.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Since they shed the bloodof your holy people and your prophets,you
        have given them blood to drink.It is their just reward.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And I heard a voice from the altar,[[COMMENT(0)]] saying,\u201CYes,
        O Lord God, the Almighty,your judgments are true and just.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '16:7 '
        content: Greek <b>I heard the altar.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the fourth angel poured out his bowl on the sun, causing it
        to scorch everyone with its fire. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Everyone was burned by this blast of heat, and they cursed the name
        of God, who had control over all these plagues. They did not repent of their
        sins and turn to God and give him glory.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the fifth angel poured out his bowl on the throne of the beast,
        and his kingdom was plunged into darkness. His subjects ground their teeth[[COMMENT(0)]]
        in anguish, '
      comments:
      - number: '16:10 '
        content: Greek <b>gnawed their tongues.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'and they cursed the God of heaven for their pains and sores. But
        they did not repent of their evil deeds and turn to God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the sixth angel poured out his bowl on the great Euphrates River,
        and it dried up so that the kings from the east could march their armies
        toward the west without hindrance. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And I saw three evil[[COMMENT(0)]] spirits that looked like frogs
        leap from the mouths of the dragon, the beast, and the false prophet. '
      comments:
      - number: '16:13 '
        content: Greek <b>unclean.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'They are demonic spirits who work miracles and go out to all the
        rulers of the world to gather them for battle against the Lord on that great
        judgment day of God the Almighty.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CLook, I will come as unexpectedly as a thief! Blessed are
        all who are watching for me, who keep their clothing ready so they will not
        have to walk around naked and ashamed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And the demonic spirits gathered all the rulers and their armies
        to a place with the Hebrew name Armageddon.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '16:16 '
        content: Or <b>Harmagedon.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Then the seventh angel poured out his bowl into the air. And a mighty
        shout came from the throne in the Temple, saying, \u201CIt is finished!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the thunder crashed and rolled, and lightning flashed. And a
        great earthquake struck\u2014the worst since people were placed on the earth. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The great city of Babylon split into three sections, and the cities
        of many nations fell into heaps of rubble. So God remembered all of Babylon\u2019s
        sins, and he made her drink the cup that was filled with the wine of his
        fierce wrath. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And every island disappeared, and all the mountains were leveled. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Great Prostitute
      content: "  One of the seven angels who had poured out the seven bowls came
        over and spoke to me. \u201CCome with me,\u201D he said, \u201Cand I will
        show you the judgment that is going to come on the great prostitute, who
        rules over many waters. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The kings of the world have committed adultery with her, and the
        people who belong to this world have been made drunk by the wine of her immorality.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So the angel took me in the Spirit[[COMMENT(0)]] into the wilderness.
        There I saw a woman sitting on a scarlet beast that had seven heads and ten
        horns, and blasphemies against God were written all over it. '
      comments:
      - number: '17:3 '
        content: Or <b>in spirit.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'The woman wore purple and scarlet clothing and beautiful jewelry
        made of gold and precious gems and pearls. In her hand she held a gold goblet
        full of obscenities and the impurities of her immorality. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A mysterious name was written on her forehead: \u201CBabylon the
        Great, Mother of All Prostitutes and Obscenities in the World.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I could see that she was drunk\u2014drunk with the blood of God\u2019s
        holy people who were witnesses for Jesus. I stared at her in complete amazement.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhy are you so amazed?\u201D the angel asked. \u201CI will
        tell you the mystery of this woman and of the beast with seven heads and
        ten horns on which she sits. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The beast you saw was once alive but isn\u2019t now. And yet he will
        soon come up out of the bottomless pit[[COMMENT(0)]] and go to eternal destruction.
        And the people who belong to this world, whose names were not written in
        the Book of Life before the world was made, will be amazed at the reappearance
        of this beast who had died.  "
      comments:
      - number: '17:8 '
        content: Or <b>the abyss, </b>or <b>the underworld.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis calls for a mind with understanding: The seven heads of
        the beast represent the seven hills where the woman rules. They also represent
        seven kings. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Five kings have already fallen, the sixth now reigns, and the seventh
        is yet to come, but his reign will be brief.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe scarlet beast that was, but is no longer, is the eighth
        king. He is like the other seven, and he, too, is headed for destruction. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The ten horns of the beast are ten kings who have not yet risen to
        power. They will be appointed to their kingdoms for one brief moment to reign
        with the beast. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will all agree to give him their power and authority. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Together they will go to war against the Lamb, but the Lamb will
        defeat them because he is Lord of all lords and King of all kings. And his
        called and chosen and faithful ones will be with him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the angel said to me, \u201CThe waters where the prostitute
        is ruling represent masses of people of every nation and language. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The scarlet beast and his ten horns all hate the prostitute. They
        will strip her naked, eat her flesh, and burn her remains with fire. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For God has put a plan into their minds, a plan that will carry out
        his purposes. They will agree to give their authority to the scarlet beast,
        and so the words of God will be fulfilled. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Fall of Babylon
      content: '  After all this I saw another angel come down from heaven with great
        authority, and the earth grew bright with his splendor. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He gave a mighty shout:\u201CBabylon is fallen\u2014that great city
        is fallen!She has become a home for demons.She is a hideout for every foul[[COMMENT(0)]]
        spirit,a hideout for every foul vultureand every foul and dreadful animal.[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '18:2a '
        content: Greek <b>unclean; </b>also in each of the two following phrases.
      - number: '18:2b '
        content: Some manuscripts condense the last two lines to read <b>a hideout
          for every foul [unclean] and dreadful vulture.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "For all the nations have fallen[[COMMENT(0)]]because of the wine
        of her passionate immorality.The kings of the worldhave committed adultery
        with her.Because of her desires for extravagant luxury,the merchants of the
        world have grown rich.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '18:3 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>have drunk.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Then I heard another voice calling from heaven,\u201CCome away from
        her, my people.Do not take part in her sins,or you will be punished with
        her.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For her sins are piled as high as heaven,and God remembers her evil
        deeds.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do to her as she has done to others.Double her penalty[[COMMENT(0)]]
        for all her evil deeds.She brewed a cup of terror for others,so brew twice
        as much[[COMMENT(1)]] for her.  '
      comments:
      - number: '18:6a '
        content: Or <b>Give her an equal penalty.</b>
      - number: '18:6b '
        content: Or <b>brew just as much.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "She glorified herself and lived in luxury,so match it now with torment
        and sorrow.She boasted in her heart,\u2018I am queen on my throne.I am no
        helpless widow,and I have no reason to mourn.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, these plagues will overtake her in a single day\u2014death
        and mourning and famine.She will be completely consumed by fire,for the Lord
        God who judges her is mighty.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And the kings of the world who committed adultery with her and enjoyed
        her great luxury will mourn for her as they see the smoke rising from her
        charred remains. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will stand at a distance, terrified by her great torment. They
        will cry out,\u201CHow terrible, how terrible for you,O Babylon, you great
        city!In a single momentGod\u2019s judgment came on you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The merchants of the world will weep and mourn for her, for there
        is no one left to buy their goods. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'She bought great quantities of gold, silver, jewels, and pearls;
        fine linen, purple, silk, and scarlet cloth; things made of fragrant thyine
        wood, ivory goods, and objects made of expensive wood; and bronze, iron,
        and marble. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She also bought cinnamon, spice, incense, myrrh, frankincense, wine,
        olive oil, fine flour, wheat, cattle, sheep, horses, wagons, and bodies\u2014that
        is, human slaves.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe fancy things you loved so muchare gone,\u201D they cry.\u201CAll
        your luxuries and splendorare gone forever,never to be yours again.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The merchants who became wealthy by selling her these things will
        stand at a distance, terrified by her great torment. They will weep and cry
        out,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHow terrible, how terrible for that great city!She was clothed
        in finest purple and scarlet linens,decked out with gold and precious stones
        and pearls!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In a single momentall the wealth of the city is gone!\u201DAnd all
        the captains of the merchant ships and their passengers and sailors and crews
        will stand at a distance. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will cry out as they watch the smoke ascend, and they will say,
        \u201CWhere is there another city as great as this?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And they will weep and throw dust on their heads to show their grief.
        And they will cry out,\u201CHow terrible, how terrible for that great city!The
        shipowners became wealthyby transporting her great wealth on the seas.In
        a single moment it is all gone.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Rejoice over her fate, O heavenand people of God and apostles and
        prophets!For at last God has judged herfor your sakes.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then a mighty angel picked up a boulder the size of a huge millstone.
        He threw it into the ocean and shouted,\u201CJust like this, the great city
        Babylonwill be thrown down with violenceand will never be found again.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The sound of harps, singers, flutes, and trumpetswill never be heard
        in you again.No craftsmen and no tradeswill ever be found in you again.The
        sound of the millwill never be heard in you again.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The light of a lampwill never shine in you again.The happy voices
        of brides and groomswill never be heard in you again.For your merchants were
        the greatest in the world,and you deceived the nations with your sorceries.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Songs of Victory in Heaven
      content: "  After this, I heard what sounded like a vast crowd in heaven shouting,\u201CPraise
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>![[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>Salvation and glory
        and power belong to our God.</smallcaps>  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:1 '
        content: "Greek <b>Hallelujah; </b>also in 19:3, 4, 6. <b>Hallelujah </b>is
          the transliteration of a Hebrew term that means \u201CPraise the <span
          class=\"ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf\">Lord</span>.\u201D"
    - title: 
      content: "His judgments are true and just.He has punished the great prostitutewho
        corrupted the earth with her immorality.He has avenged the murder of his
        servants.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And again their voices rang out:\u201CPraise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!The
        smoke from that city ascends forever and ever!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the twenty-four elders and the four living beings fell down
        and worshiped God, who was sitting on the throne. They cried out, \u201CAmen!
        Praise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And from the throne came a voice that said,\u201CPraise our God,all
        his servants,all who fear him,from the least to the greatest.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then I heard again what sounded like the shout of a vast crowd or
        the roar of mighty ocean waves or the crash of loud thunder:\u201CPraise
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!For the Lord our God,[[COMMENT(0)]] the Almighty,
        reigns.  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:6 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>the Lord God.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Let us be glad and rejoice,and let us give honor to him.For the time
        has come for the wedding feast of the Lamb,and his bride has prepared herself.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She has been given the finest of pure white linen to wear.\u201DFor
        the fine linen represents the good deeds of God\u2019s holy people.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And the angel said to me, \u201CWrite this: Blessed are those who
        are invited to the wedding feast of the Lamb.\u201D And he added, \u201CThese
        are true words that come from God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: The Rider on the White Horse
      content: "Then I fell down at his feet to worship him, but he said, \u201CNo,
        don\u2019t worship me. I am a servant of God, just like you and your brothers
        and sisters[[COMMENT(0)]] who testify about their faith in Jesus. Worship
        only God. For the essence of prophecy is to give a clear witness for Jesus.[[COMMENT(1)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:10a '
        content: Greek <b>brothers.</b>
      - number: '19:10b '
        content: Or <b>is the message confirmed by Jesus.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Then I saw heaven opened, and a white horse was standing there. Its
        rider was named Faithful and True, for he judges fairly and wages a righteous
        war. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'His eyes were like flames of fire, and on his head were many crowns.
        A name was written on him that no one understood except himself. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He wore a robe dipped in blood, and his title was the Word of God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The armies of heaven, dressed in the finest of pure white linen,
        followed him on white horses. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'From his mouth came a sharp sword to strike down the nations. He
        will rule them with an iron rod. He will release the fierce wrath of God,
        the Almighty, like juice flowing from a winepress. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'On his robe at his thigh[[COMMENT(0)]] was written this title: King
        of all kings and Lord of all lords.  '
      comments:
      - number: '19:16 '
        content: Or <b>On his robe and thigh.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Then I saw an angel standing in the sun, shouting to the vultures
        flying high in the sky: \u201CCome! Gather together for the great banquet
        God has prepared. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Come and eat the flesh of kings, generals, and strong warriors; of
        horses and their riders; and of all humanity, both free and slave, small
        and great.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then I saw the beast and the kings of the world and their armies
        gathered together to fight against the one sitting on the horse and his army. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And the beast was captured, and with him the false prophet who did
        mighty miracles on behalf of the beast\u2014miracles that deceived all who
        had accepted the mark of the beast and who worshiped his statue. Both the
        beast and his false prophet were thrown alive into the fiery lake of burning
        sulfur. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Thousand Years
      content: '  Then I saw an angel coming down from heaven with the key to the
        bottomless pit[[COMMENT(0)]] and a heavy chain in his hand. '
      comments:
      - number: '20:1 '
        content: Or <b>the abyss, </b>or <b>the underworld; </b>also in 20:3.
    - title: 
      content: "He seized the dragon\u2014that old serpent, who is the devil, Satan\u2014and
        bound him in chains for a thousand years. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The angel threw him into the bottomless pit, which he then shut and
        locked so Satan could not deceive the nations anymore until the thousand
        years were finished. Afterward he must be released for a little while.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then I saw thrones, and the people sitting on them had been given
        the authority to judge. And I saw the souls of those who had been beheaded
        for their testimony about Jesus and for proclaiming the word of God. They
        had not worshiped the beast or his statue, nor accepted his mark on their
        foreheads or their hands. They all came to life again, and they reigned with
        Christ for a thousand years.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This is the first resurrection. (The rest of the dead did not come
        back to life until the thousand years had ended.) '
      comments: []
    - title: The Defeat of Satan
      content: 'Blessed and holy are those who share in the first resurrection. For
        them the second death holds no power, but they will be priests of God and
        of Christ and will reign with him a thousand years.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When the thousand years come to an end, Satan will be let out of
        his prison. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He will go out to deceive the nations\u2014called Gog and Magog\u2014in
        every corner of the earth. He will gather them together for battle\u2014a
        mighty army, as numberless as sand along the seashore. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And I saw them as they went up on the broad plain of the earth and
        surrounded God\u2019s people and the beloved city. But fire from heaven came
        down on the attacking armies and consumed them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: The Final Judgment
      content: 'Then the devil, who had deceived them, was thrown into the fiery
        lake of burning sulfur, joining the beast and the false prophet. There they
        will be tormented day and night forever and ever.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And I saw a great white throne and the one sitting on it. The earth
        and sky fled from his presence, but they found no place to hide. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I saw the dead, both great and small, standing before God\u2019s
        throne. And the books were opened, including the Book of Life. And the dead
        were judged according to what they had done, as recorded in the books. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The sea gave up its dead, and death and the grave[[COMMENT(0)]] gave
        up their dead. And all were judged according to their deeds. '
      comments:
      - number: '20:13 '
        content: Greek <b>and Hades; </b>also in 20:14.
    - title: 
      content: 'Then death and the grave were thrown into the lake of fire. This
        lake of fire is the second death. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The New Jerusalem
      content: '  Then I saw a new heaven and a new earth, for the old heaven and
        the old earth had disappeared. And the sea was also gone. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And I saw the holy city, the new Jerusalem, coming down from God
        out of heaven like a bride beautifully dressed for her husband.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I heard a loud shout from the throne, saying, \u201CLook, God\u2019s
        home is now among his people! He will live with them, and they will be his
        people. God himself will be with them.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '21:3 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>God himself will be with them, their God.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "He will wipe every tear from their eyes, and there will be no more
        death or sorrow or crying or pain. All these things are gone forever.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And the one sitting on the throne said, \u201CLook, I am making everything
        new!\u201D And then he said to me, \u201CWrite this down, for what I tell
        you is trustworthy and true.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And he also said, \u201CIt is finished! I am the Alpha and the Omega\u2014the
        Beginning and the End. To all who are thirsty I will give freely from the
        springs of the water of life. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'All who are victorious will inherit all these blessings, and I will
        be their God, and they will be my children.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut cowards, unbelievers, the corrupt, murderers, the immoral,
        those who practice witchcraft, idol worshipers, and all liars\u2014their
        fate is in the fiery lake of burning sulfur. This is the second death.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then one of the seven angels who held the seven bowls containing
        the seven last plagues came and said to me, \u201CCome with me! I will show
        you the bride, the wife of the Lamb.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So he took me in the Spirit[[COMMENT(0)]] to a great, high mountain,
        and he showed me the holy city, Jerusalem, descending out of heaven from
        God. '
      comments:
      - number: '21:10 '
        content: Or <b>in spirit.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "It shone with the glory of God and sparkled like a precious stone\u2014like
        jasper as clear as crystal. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The city wall was broad and high, with twelve gates guarded by twelve
        angels. And the names of the twelve tribes of Israel were written on the
        gates. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "There were three gates on each side\u2014east, north, south, and
        west. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The wall of the city had twelve foundation stones, and on them were
        written the names of the twelve apostles of the Lamb.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The angel who talked to me held in his hand a gold measuring stick
        to measure the city, its gates, and its wall. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When he measured it, he found it was a square, as wide as it was
        long. In fact, its length and width and height were each 1,400 miles.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '21:16 '
        content: Greek <b>12,000 stadia </b>[2,220 kilometers].
    - title: 
      content: 'Then he measured the walls and found them to be 216 feet thick[[COMMENT(0)]]
        (according to the human standard used by the angel).  '
      comments:
      - number: '21:17 '
        content: Greek <b>144 cubits </b>[65 meters].
    - title: 
      content: 'The wall was made of jasper, and the city was pure gold, as clear
        as glass. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The wall of the city was built on foundation stones inlaid with twelve
        precious stones:[[COMMENT(0)]] the first was jasper, the second sapphire,
        the third agate, the fourth emerald, '
      comments:
      - number: '21:19 '
        content: The identification of some of these gemstones is uncertain.
    - title: 
      content: 'the fifth onyx, the sixth carnelian, the seventh chrysolite, the
        eighth beryl, the ninth topaz, the tenth chrysoprase, the eleventh jacinth,
        the twelfth amethyst.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The twelve gates were made of pearls\u2014each gate from a single
        pearl! And the main street was pure gold, as clear as glass.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I saw no temple in the city, for the Lord God Almighty and the Lamb
        are its temple. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And the city has no need of sun or moon, for the glory of God illuminates
        the city, and the Lamb is its light. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The nations will walk in its light, and the kings of the world will
        enter the city in all their glory. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Its gates will never be closed at the end of day because there is
        no night there. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And all the nations will bring their glory and honor into the city. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  Then the angel showed me a river with the water of life, clear
        as crystal, flowing from the throne of God and of the Lamb. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It flowed down the center of the main street. On each side of the
        river grew a tree of life, bearing twelve crops of fruit,[[COMMENT(0)]] with
        a fresh crop each month. The leaves were used for medicine to heal the nations.  '
      comments:
      - number: '22:2 '
        content: Or <b>twelve kinds of fruit.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'No longer will there be a curse upon anything. For the throne of
        God and of the Lamb will be there, and his servants will worship him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And they will see his face, and his name will be written on their
        foreheads. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And there will be no night there\u2014no need for lamps or sun\u2014for
        the Lord God will shine on them. And they will reign forever and ever.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Is Coming
      content: "Then the angel said to me, \u201CEverything you have heard and seen
        is trustworthy and true. The Lord God, who inspires his prophets,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        has sent his angel to tell his servants what will happen soon.[[COMMENT(1)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '22:6a '
        content: Or <b>The Lord, the God of the spirits of the prophets.</b>
      - number: '22:6b '
        content: 'Or <b>suddenly</b>, or <b>quickly; </b>also in 22:7, 12, 20.  '
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CLook, I am coming soon! Blessed are those who obey the words
        of prophecy written in this book.  [[COMMENT(0)]]  \u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '22:7 '
        content: '  Or   <b>scroll</b>  ; also in 22:9, 10, 18, 19.    '
    - title: 
      content: 'I, John, am the one who heard and saw all these things. And when
        I heard and saw them, I fell down to worship at the feet of the angel who
        showed them to me. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But he said, \u201CNo, don\u2019t worship me. I am a servant of God,
        just like you and your brothers the prophets, as well as all who obey what
        is written in this book. Worship only God!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then he instructed me, \u201CDo not seal up the prophetic words in
        this book, for the time is near. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Let the one who is doing harm continue to do harm; let the one who
        is vile continue to be vile; let the one who is righteous continue to live
        righteously; let the one who is holy continue to be holy.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CLook, I am coming soon, bringing my reward with me to repay
        all people according to their deeds.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I am the Alpha and the Omega, the First and the Last, the Beginning
        and the End.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Blessed are those who wash their robes. They will be permitted to
        enter through the gates of the city and eat the fruit from the tree of life. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Outside the city are the dogs\u2014the sorcerers, the sexually immoral,
        the murderers, the idol worshipers, and all who love to live a lie.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CI, Jesus, have sent my angel to give you this message for
        the churches. I am both the source of David and the heir to his throne. 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  I am the bright morning star.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '22:16 '
        content: '  Greek   <b>I am the root and offspring of David.</b>  '
    - title: 
      content: "The Spirit and the bride say, \u201CCome.\u201D Let anyone who hears
        this say, \u201CCome.\u201D Let anyone who is thirsty come. Let anyone who
        desires drink freely from the water of life. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And I solemnly declare to everyone who hears the words of prophecy
        written in this book: If anyone adds anything to what is written here, God
        will add to that person the plagues described in this book. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And if anyone removes any of the words from this book of prophecy,
        God will remove that person\u2019s share in the tree of life and in the holy
        city that are described in this book.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He who is the faithful witness to all these things says, \u201CYes,
        I am coming soon!\u201DAmen! Come, Lord Jesus!  "
      comments: []
